         <div>
            <head>15.4.1882 Samstag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49096">Paris</placeName> April 15.
      1882. Saturday</p>
            <p> Went to a concert this evening. The first piece which was played by the
      author (<persName key="1127">Chaminade</persName>) who has got hair like a nigger and ought
      to be locked up as a malefactrice of mankind was something awful; there was no
      pretence at melody or harmony in it or if there was it is no flattery to the
      author: to begin with the &#x201e;accords&#x201c; were discordant in themselves
      and were not connected with the next note in any way whatsoever; then the
      violin the base and the piano seemed to be, no not seemed to be but
      <hi rend="ul">were</hi> playing utterly different pieces which clashed
      together dreadfully at times. Every particularly discordant accord was played
      or rather thumped louder than the rest of the piece as much as to say
      &#x201e;There now; there is something pretty for you&#x201c; When she had
      finished the authoress got up looked very pleased with herself and her piece
      and majestically swept out of the room.</p>
         </div>
